# 4.0.x: RECOVERED (see VERSIONS.md, iteration 5). zsh's ZLE "get-line" widget
# is a C function literally named getline(), whose generated prototype conflicts
# with musl stdio.h's POSIX getline() ("conflicting types for 'getline'"). A
# -Dgetline=... macro can't fix it (it would rename musl's declaration too), so
# patches/zsh/<v>/001-rename-getline.diff renames the widget function to
# zlegetline (definition + Src/Zle/iwidgets.list; the .epro prototype is
# regenerated from the .c). The series filter keeps 4.0.9 as the 4.0
# representative. No longer excluded.

# Still excluded below the 4.0 series:
# 3.1.x - configure.in references an undefined m4 macro (zsh-debug) that aborts
#         autom4te, plus the same preconfig/getline-era breakage.
# 3.0.8 - older source layout with no ./Util/preconfig, which shvr_build_zsh
#         requires; the build recipe cannot drive this tree.
3.1.9
3.1.8
3.1.7
